# Component Library Code Review Rules

## Context & Architecture

Modern React component library requiring careful review of:
- **Component Layer**: Reusable, composable components with proper APIs
- **Styling Layer**: CSS integration and theming
- **Accessibility Layer**: ARIA compliance and keyboard navigation
- **Distribution Layer**: Build output, TypeScript definitions, and tree-shaking

## Review Priority Matrix

### Critical (Must Fix)
- Accessibility violations (missing ARIA, keyboard navigation)
- Breaking API changes without proper versioning
- Runtime errors or infinite re-renders
- Bundle size regressions affecting tree-shaking
- TypeScript definition errors

### High Priority (Should Fix)
- Component API inconsistencies
- Missing prop validation or default values
- Styling conflicts or theming issues
- Performance issues (unnecessary re-renders)
- Missing error boundaries

### Medium Priority (Consider)
- Documentation completeness
- Test coverage gaps
- Code organization and maintainability
- Developer experience improvements

## Layer-Specific Review Guidelines

### Component Layer (React/API Design)

**API Consistency**
```typescript
// ❌ Bad: Inconsistent prop naming
interface ButtonProps {
  isLoading?: boolean;
  disabled?: boolean;
  color?: string;
}

// ✅ Good: Consistent patterns
interface ButtonProps {
  loading?: boolean;
  disabled?: boolean;
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
}
```

**Composition Patterns**
- Verify compound component relationships
- Check forwardRef usage for DOM access
- Review polymorphic component implementations
- Ensure proper children handling

**Performance Optimization**
```typescript
// ❌ Bad: New object every render
const Component = ({ items }) => {
  const config = { mode: 'default', items };
  return <List config={config} />;
};

// ✅ Good: Memoized stable references
const Component = ({ items }) => {
  const config = useMemo(() => ({ mode: 'default', items }), [items]);
  return <List config={config} />;
};
```

### Styling Layer (CSS/Theming)

**Theme Integration**
- Review CSS custom property usage
- Check dark mode compatibility
- Verify responsive design patterns
- Ensure style encapsulation

**Tailwind/Styling Best Practices**
```typescript
// ❌ Bad: Hardcoded styles
const Button = ({ variant }) => (
  <button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2">
    {children}
  </button>
);

// ✅ Good: Dynamic styling with variants
const buttonVariants = cva("px-4 py-2 rounded", {
  variants: {
    variant: {
      primary: "bg-blue-500 text-white",
      secondary: "bg-gray-200 text-gray-900"
    }
  }
});
```

### Accessibility Layer (A11y/UX)

**ARIA Compliance**
```typescript
// ❌ Bad: Missing accessibility features
const Dialog = ({ open, children }) => (
  <div style={{ display: open ? 'block' : 'none' }}>
    {children}
  </div>
);

// ✅ Good: Proper ARIA and focus management
const Dialog = ({ open, children, onClose }) => (
  <div
    role="dialog"
    aria-modal="true"
    aria-hidden={!open}
    onKeyDown={(e) => e.key === 'Escape' && onClose()}
  >
    {children}
  </div>
);
```

**Keyboard Navigation**
- Verify tab order and focus management
- Check keyboard event handling
- Review screen reader compatibility
- Ensure proper focus indicators

### Distribution Layer (Build/Types)

**TypeScript Definitions**
- Review exported type accuracy
- Check generic constraints and inference
- Verify prop type completeness
- Ensure backward compatibility

**Build Configuration**
```typescript
// ✅ Good: Proper export patterns
export { Button } from './Button';
export type { ButtonProps } from './Button';

// Tree-shaking friendly
export * from './components';
```

## Code Quality Standards

### Component API Criteria
- Consistent prop naming across components
- Sensible defaults for optional props
- Clear prop validation and TypeScript types
- Polymorphic components where appropriate

### Performance Standards
- No unnecessary re-renders
- Bundle size impact under 5KB per component
- Tree-shaking friendly exports
- Efficient CSS-in-JS usage

### Accessibility Requirements
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader compatibility
- High contrast mode support

## Review Process Workflow

### 1. Automated Checks
```bash
# Type checking and linting
pnpm typecheck
pnpm lint

# Component testing
pnpm test

# Bundle analysis
pnpm analyze
```

### 2. Manual Review Categories

**Component Quality**
- [ ] API follows library conventions
- [ ] Props are properly typed and documented
- [ ] Component is accessible by default
- [ ] Styling integrates with theme system

**Integration Testing**
- [ ] Works with form libraries
- [ ] Integrates with routing solutions
- [ ] Compatible with SSR/SSG
- [ ] No hydration mismatches

**Developer Experience**
- [ ] Clear TypeScript intellisense
- [ ] Helpful error messages
- [ ] Documentation examples work
- [ ] Storybook stories comprehensive

### 3. Specialized Reviews

**Design System Review**
- Token usage consistency
- Component variant completeness
- Brand guideline compliance
- Cross-component harmony

**Accessibility Review**
- ARIA pattern implementation
- Keyboard interaction testing
- Screen reader testing
- Color contrast verification

## Review Completion Checklist

- [ ] All automated tests pass
- [ ] Accessibility audit shows no violations
- [ ] TypeScript definitions export correctly
- [ ] Bundle size impact acceptable
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Storybook examples added
- [ ] Cross-browser compatibility verified
- [ ] Mobile responsiveness tested
- [ ] SSR compatibility confirmed
- [ ] Breaking changes properly versioned